sql:
SELECT is_shared
FROM command_templates
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "garden of commands" refers to the database of command logs;
- "cast more than five spells" means the user has more than 5 log entries;
- "most patient user" refers to the user with the highest average command execution duration.

- 'Guardians of the digital realm' refers to users with the 'admin' role;
- 'Analysts' refers to users with the 'analyst' role;
- The cumulative duration is the total time spent executing commands, calculated as the sum of individual command execution durations for each user.

- 'Casting the spell of encryption' refers to executing encryption commands;
- 'Successfully cast' means the command execution has a status code of 0, indicating success;
- 'Analysts' are users with the role 'analyst'.

- 'Stumbled upon the path of failed login attempts more than twice' means the user has more than two failed login attempts;
- 'Last encountered a stumbling block after the gates of May 2023 opened' means the user's latest error occurred after May 1, 2023;
- 'The most command errors' refers to the user with the highest number of errors.

- "shining star" refers to the most frequently used command;
- "top 3 most frequently wielded" refers to the commands with the highest usage counts for each admin, limited to the top 3;
- "most beloved by the collective" refers to the command with the highest usage count across all admins.

- 'Gardeners' refer to users in the system;
- 'Tools' refer to roles assigned to users;
- 'Successfully tended to the plants' refers to successful command executions with a status code of 0;
- 'How many times they have done so' refers to the count of successful command executions.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(template_id) 
FROM command_templates
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Active users who have blossomed in the past month' refers to users with `is_active = 1` and `last_login` within the last month;
- 'Commands have been cast more than five times' means the `COUNT(*)` of command executions is greater than 5;
- 'Encryption commands' refers to commands with `command_type = 'encryption'`.

- 'SpecificCommandName' is a placeholder for a particular command name;
- 'admins' refers to users with the role 'admin';
- 'past month' is defined as the last 30 days from the current date.
